wllppr
________________________________________________________________________________

A simple script that downloads images from `unsplash.com`
and sets them using `pywal`


requirements
________________________________________________________________________________

POSIX sh
curl
pywal


installation
________________________________________________________________________________

To install place `wllppr` within a directory in $PATH


configuration
________________________________________________________________________________

# User based options
export WLLPPR_USER="user_name" # Get a certain user's collection
export WLLPPR_LIKED="true"     # Get the liked images of said user

# Toggle featured images
export WLLPPR_FEATURED="true"

# What dimension to use
export WLLPPR_DIMENSION="1920x1080"

# Use search terms
export WLLPPR_SEARCH_TAGS="dog,cat,lol" # Comma separated search terms
                                        # to be used with WLLPPR_DIMENSION
                                        # and WLLPPR_FEATURED

why?
________________________________________________________________________________

Just cos i needed a script that changes the
wallpaper when i tell it to using pywal
